Six people were injured, two of them critically, after they were stung by a swarm of bees in Ballito on Thursday morning. IPSS Medical Rescue, together with Lenmed paramedics, attended the scene. “Advanced life support paramedics responded to the scene a short while ago and determined that workers had been mowing the lawn when they disturbed a beehive. A total of six people were stung with two of them being critical and requiring advanced life support intervention.” The men were stabilised then taken to hospital.